<section id="section7" data-total="10">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
            <h2 class="colour2">What's New at Abacus?</h2>
            <span class="bg-colour1"></span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="record-slider">
        <div class="slider-container">
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="109">
                        <time>29/08/2025</time>
                        <h3>What an adventure our K1 children have been on! After spending some time in school with their families, getting to know the teaching team and the new learning spaces, they are now so much more confident coming to school.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/025cb6117c2d26ea830306ea0e4ca6f5.jpg" alt="539415797_18129688276459578_1746173094247902946_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="108">
                        <time>28/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>A snapshot of how the learning in K1 was documented during the children's inquiry into how they can respond to ideas, experiences and their thinking. By listening carefully to the children and celebrating their chosen play, we learn so much.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/61d2ae22967fa71a580f57021ba157ed.jpg" alt="511614862_18123944071459578_7616166188364019034_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="107">
                        <time>28/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>As part of their inquiry, the children have explored colour mixing to find what they saw as the right tones to paint their skin. They enjoyed adding different materials to complete their self-portraits.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/f2762b5b85af5924526a7abc828add3c.jpg" alt="513513447_18123943708459578_2002386403741613699_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="106">
                        <time>28/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>A snapshot of some of the learning environment used to stimulate the children's interest and document their learning during their inquiry into how they can express their ideas and respond to experiences.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/c7f21508752fda102f4c4eebeb4a5094.jpg" alt="504389074_18123943591459578_5374418410375674426_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="105">
                        <time>27/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>The children's inquiry into the different ways that people share their ideas and feelings has led to lots of exploration of different ways to use colour. Spray bottles of coloured paint have brought about so much joy and conversation as the colours mix. <br>We have also seen the K1 children dancing and singing at every opportunity. We are grateful to Josh from Move For Life for his energy and enthusiasm as he led the children and their families through some moves during the Celebration of Learning! @moveforlife.asia</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/55522464181890a37ca1c89d9fd1f545.jpg" alt="511564424_18123907195459578_6837311370162696408_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="104">
                        <time>27/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>Our K1 learners loved welcoming their families into school for their final Celebration of Learning for the year. The environment was an invitation to the children to share how and what they had learned in their latest inquiry into How We Express Ourselves. Listening to the children's play, you could see and hear their growth this year as learners. They showed their self-management skills as they chose tools and selected materials to make mark-making with, their social skills as they interacted with their classmates, and their creative thinking was everywhere. We heard parents asking reflective questions like "What are you proud of?" "How did you decide to choose that colour?" "Where did you get that idea from?". It was lovely to see the engagement. Thank you to all the families who came. #familypartnership #PYPEarlyYears</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/8670bc0f1ca14f16f254c6d7b577fd6d.jpg" alt="502556417_18123906376459578_5653806149878729250_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="103">
                        <time>27/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>A big well done to our K2 children and thank you to our families for visiting school this week to celebrate all of the children's learning. The children shared the performances, artwork and stories that they created during their inquiry into How We Express Ourselves. #PYPlearners</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/a96f9cfeb7df9b93e817f987ad21ddb8.jpg" alt="504357613_18123904408459578_1025449605985823968_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="102">
                        <time>27/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>What a great way to end the year! Splash Day is a favourite for everyone at Abacus- children and teaching team alike.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/9f366fb9f0676ec5031dcd6d387c8028.jpg" alt="503474693_18123903991459578_626819279839764764_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="101">
                        <time>27/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>Splash Day at Abacus! A yearly tradition to end the year, and so much fun is had by children and staff alike. The giggles and excitement as the children explore all the water play are wonderful to hear.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/876653fa8915febb829a83714b5d4d7a.jpg" alt="504284850_18123903499459578_6885753284990929084_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="100">
                        <time>27/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>Families got artistic on our K2 sharing day and created some lovely keepsakes to celebrate the end of the children's Abacus adventures. We wish all our graduates the best of luck as they move on to primary school.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/64b3af71ecb3361b3d9838561b1584d7.jpg" alt="503611697_18123877594459578_4314588971882530901_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="109">
                        <time>29/08/2025</time>
                        <h3>What an adventure our K1 children have been on! After spending some time in school with their families, getting to know the teaching team and the new learning spaces, they are now so much more confident coming to school.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/025cb6117c2d26ea830306ea0e4ca6f5.jpg" alt="539415797_18129688276459578_1746173094247902946_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="108">
                        <time>28/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>A snapshot of how the learning in K1 was documented during the children's inquiry into how they can respond to ideas, experiences and their thinking. By listening carefully to the children and celebrating their chosen play, we learn so much.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/61d2ae22967fa71a580f57021ba157ed.jpg" alt="511614862_18123944071459578_7616166188364019034_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="107">
                        <time>28/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>As part of their inquiry, the children have explored colour mixing to find what they saw as the right tones to paint their skin. They enjoyed adding different materials to complete their self-portraits.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/f2762b5b85af5924526a7abc828add3c.jpg" alt="513513447_18123943708459578_2002386403741613699_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="106">
                        <time>28/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>A snapshot of some of the learning environment used to stimulate the children's interest and document their learning during their inquiry into how they can express their ideas and respond to experiences.</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/c7f21508752fda102f4c4eebeb4a5094.jpg" alt="504389074_18123943591459578_5374418410375674426_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="105">
                        <time>27/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>The children's inquiry into the different ways that people share their ideas and feelings has led to lots of exploration of different ways to use colour. Spray bottles of coloured paint have brought about so much joy and conversation as the colours mix. <br>We have also seen the K1 children dancing and singing at every opportunity. We are grateful to Josh from Move For Life for his energy and enthusiasm as he led the children and their families through some moves during the Celebration of Learning! @moveforlife.asia</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/55522464181890a37ca1c89d9fd1f545.jpg" alt="511564424_18123907195459578_6837311370162696408_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
                            <div class="post-item">
                    <div class="post" data-id="104">
                        <time>27/06/2025</time>
                        <h3>Our K1 learners loved welcoming their families into school for their final Celebration of Learning for the year. The environment was an invitation to the children to share how and what they had learned in their latest inquiry into How We Express Ourselves. Listening to the children's play, you could see and hear their growth this year as learners. They showed their self-management skills as they chose tools and selected materials to make mark-making with, their social skills as they interacted with their classmates, and their creative thinking was everywhere. We heard parents asking reflective questions like "What are you proud of?" "How did you decide to choose that colour?" "Where did you get that idea from?". It was lovely to see the engagement. Thank you to all the families who came. #familypartnership #PYPEarlyYears</h3>
                        <button>Read more</button>
                        <img src="/cache/img/8670bc0f1ca14f16f254c6d7b577fd6d.jpg" alt="502556417_18123906376459578_5653806149878729250_n" loading="lazy" width="682" height="682" />                    </div>
                </div>
